mcqs.question:
What is the output of the following C++ code?

int i = 0;
while (i < 3) {
    cout << i << " ";
    i++;
}

In the following nested loop structure, what will be printed?

for (int i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < 3; j++) {
        if (j == 1) continue;
        cout << i << j << " ";
    }
}

Identify the bug in the following code intended to find the sum of numbers from 1 to 10:

int sum = 0;
for (int i = 1; i < 10; i++) {
    sum += i;
}

Which of the following is more efficient and why?

// Version A
for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) { }

// Version B
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) { }

What will be the output of this code?

int count = 0;
for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++) {
    for (int j = 0; j < 4; j++) {
        if (i == j) break;
        count++;
    }
}
cout << count;

Consider the following code. Which scenario can lead to an infinite loop (assuming no break statements)?

int i = 10;
while (i != 0) {
    i--;
}

int j = 0;
while (j < 10) {
    j--;
}
